Having so many different map types available is a definite plus and being able to download them for offline use is priceless (I did notice that with the latest Nov 2020 update that it seems not to recognize/use map downloads from earlier versions consistently). Overall I recommend this app hands down over other apps of its type. You will need to have a fair amount of understanding of how to read maps and orienteering to get the most out of it. Two features I would love to see would be the ability to create a waypoint from the EXIF data of images and store a field in each GPS trackpoint of cell signal strength (although I don't know if such a field is part of the GPX/KML standards). This app rocks!

replyContent: Dear Steve, we have answered your emails from March 28th, May 5th and today. You need to start track recording ( the button with the red point) to start the odometer. After GPS-Signal is found you'll find data fields on your map. If odometer is not present in datafield you need to click the small menu symbol in data field and set it to odometer.

I purchased the app to use as a standalone topo map for hiking in wilderness area that are way out of wifi access. You cannot search for places. Common names for places are not listed. Love, love, love this app. Reliable and works flawlessly.

what I wanted was an app that I can preload the maps and run the phone on no big brother Google watching. I wanted to have a backup device to get a view of where I am to where I am going. I preloaded all the states around me and cached the landscape maps. for where I want to be when Google starts the rounding up of thought criminals and sends them to room 101 or the googlages. if you are expecting this app to route you around the trails at the dog park or give you turn by turns like a standard road gps go download Google maps. if you are looking for a pocket topo and so much more. this is a good app for you. my only suggestions are to add nation wide storm sewers maps. and improve the watershed maps. and make chaching maps a little easier to over lay back on to your GPS mode.

Fantastic. Extremely easy to use, love the tracking feature. Very accurate. Love being able to download maps for local use. Only thing I'd like added is an account system so when you get a new device your prior tracks are still available.

replyContent: You need to deactivate energy save mode. Please do navigation drawer/preferences/system check (upper right) to check.

Great app for importing gpx files to use offline for hiking in the back country. Well worth pro upgrade.

Easily the best topographic map app out there--feature-rich, reasonably priced, easy to use, etc. Several friends picked up the pro version after I recommended it to them. But a few friends have iPhones, and there doesn't appear to be a version out there for them. Something for the developers to consider.

I've been using US Topo Maps Pro for 5 years now. I've also searched for others during that time, and have not found a more suitable application for what US Topo Maps has been able to do for one main reason. US Topo Maps has a selection of the most detailed aerial maps available. I have been able to download any map, to any device that I have needed for traveling Off-Road. From Phablets, to tablets, to standard size phones. Creating a route or track has also been a breeze. I can select any detailed map to create my route, and switch back and forth between others to ensure the route I am creating is the most accurate, and the GPS accuracy has always been + or - 10 feet. There are 2 additions I would like to make. The ability to select the highest level desired to be downloaded. When I am downloading a large area, such as the Grand Canyon Parashant National Monument, the maps take up large amounts of space. 30gb from Mesquite NV to Kelly Point Overlook. (ESRI Aerial, 11-18) Also, the ability to select only a portion of the area would also decrease the size of the maps greatly by allowing me to select only the aerial maps that I require, and not just a general square size.

Very useful, especially for hiking out of cell service range (using cache option). However, not very intuitive and minimal help within the app. Been trying to find out if latest release is compatible with Android 10??
Very useful

Unacceptable. I paid for the Pro version of this app and it crashed when I attempted to put a different map layer onto the data that I had collected. Three hours of data. Gone. Because your app froze and crash. On professional time. What are you gonna do about this? Because this is unacceptable.
replyContent: Please contact support@atlogis.com

Still I take map and compass and understand orienteering thoroughly. Take the time to learn this App. It is quite indepth and provides everything needed to navigate.

Used Pro version while turkey hunting in the mountains of central Virginia. The ridge systems coming off these mountains can be complex and hidden from view, even in daylight. US Topo worked flawlessly for me as I negotiated these ridges in the dark, hours before daylight. Some of these excursions were into unknown areas that I negotiated by following multiple waypoints I installed months earlier from 400 hundred miles away! These Waypoints proved to be accurate. Never touched paper maps.

I love the unlimited waypoint plotting , track log, and variety of maps. I hike in the deep ozarks of Missouri, and the shawnee national forest in southern Illinois, and can hunt down awesome waterfalls (in the rainy season) just using the topo maps

1. Making new points is extremely tedious as the "-" and "." keys are in secondary menus 2. ALL points regularly disappear off the map and must be reloaded 3. User location does not automatically update and, therefore, it's easy to to lose track of where you are 5. Only cached maps that I'm aware of 6. NO RESPONSE from customer support when bringing up some of these issues previously

replyContent: Please try to get with Google Maps (or any other GPS app) a GPS position. If it works it will work as well with our app as both apps use the same location service. If it doesn't work you may have a hardware problem.

content: The app is great but now that I moved to Europe, it is pretty much useless for me. @ATLOGIS Team: Is there a similar app for Europe that I could use or do you plan to add maps to this app? Thank you for your quick response. I didn't know about the other maps. It seems to work fine with open topo maps as well. So, problem solved. :)
replyContent: You can use the US Topo map in Europa as well, eg with the Open Street Maps layer. Currently we have also apps for Spain, Sweden, Denmark and UK. Other countries will follow.

content: This is absolutely the best app that I have found for hiking! I don't know how they do it, but there have been some new trails added in my area and they are already on the map. The pro version allows for caching routes and offline map downloads. It works very well. All the important functions are there. As long as you have gps input you will be able to record your track while en route. You can also plan and create a route, offline.   The database of maps available is extensive and includes multiple options (including open source and esri databases) for identifying trails and where they fork, with good enough accuracy.   One basic thing the tutorial fails to mention, is that in order to activate a route, the app needs to find the GPS. Your android phone or tablet has a setting for location. This of course must be turned on. But the key is to make sure that the accuracy setting (a location option) is set to 'on/high accuracy', and not set to 'battery saving mode'. This will  ensure that your device's GPS will be found, which is what the app needs to see - in battery saving mode the app can't find the GPS because the GPS isn't turned on. Your device only gets it's location input, in battery saving mode from your network connection.  That said, everything should work as described. The alternative to a geo-referencing application, such as this one and others like it, is to take a photo of the trail system you are hiking and reference it wherever a fork in the trail appears. If the trail is marked accurately, you could use a compass and time the distances from point a to point b, at intervals along the way (dead-reckoning). This is okay, but if the trail forks are unmarked or missing, it's anyone's guess where you will end up.   Electronic navigation is great as long as the trail maps are good and as long as your GPS has coverage. Since you can download and cache maps in this app you won't have to worry about a wifi connection to load your detailed maps while in a remote area with poor wifi or cell coverage.  I like the options that this app presents and I am giving it a 4-star rating, instead of 5 stars, because tech support from the developers of this app, is poor. They never returned an email technical request for help, on enabling the 'start route' or 'go-to' function. The app works well but you'll probably need to be a reasonable trouble-shooter, on your own, if you can't sort something out easily. Don't expect any customer service. For instance, it took me a while to sort out that the location setting on the device needed to be set for high accuracy to  enable to the 'start route' or 'go-to' functions. This wasn't described in the tutorial or help sections and tech support was unresponsive. Too bad.  But overall, it is a very nice little app, and think it is well worth having if you spend any time in mapped wilderness or remote areas and want to confirm that the way you're on, is the way you intended.

No other app comes close to the level of detail,reliability,UI,and customization as this app,when it comes to navigation. I recommend this app to EVERYONE that wanders out into the country, be it exploring,hunting,hiking,camping or a road trip, you will be satisfied in every sense of the word map. I love it!

I use this app for hiking in upstate New York.  Works great on my phone and doesn't drain the battery heavily.  I am able track and save my routes and waypoints quickly and easily.  It's also great that you don't need a cell phone signal because it relies on gps. It's also easy to share and export routes and waypoints via email to other people or my tablet which I also have this app on for better viewing and hike planning/analysis. Just remember to cache some maps before you go if you won't have reception.
Worth every penny

Awesome map for getting off the beaten path. Cache and go. Use it for Adventure Touring on the motorbike for all kinds of terrain. Freeways to Twisty pavers to trails without the need for cell service. GPX, KML, KMZ... All will work.

Could you please add a layer of geologic maps to the database.  I've tried to add my own but they fail every time.  The USGS has multiple databases with state and local geologic maps.  Please make this available, thanks!!

Love the ability to download topographic maps (for free), since I am frequently without cell coverage. Use them (and GPS, if available) as supplemental backups and supplements to my physical maps and compass). Downloaded maps can be stored to SD card for those who have that option.

I use this all the time both for navigation and for educational reasons. Having this many different maps is surprisingly useful. It's also a lot more useful as a GPS app than my GPS apps, I know that weird but it says a lot about how well this is made.

Don't spend your money on this app!!!  The maps are over 40 years old and of little use today. Of all of the maps that the app claims are available, only 4 can be loaded. This is trash and the maker of the app knows it but decided to take your money anyway.

Great app! The simplicity / aesthetics are especially nice, compared to the competition. My one request would be higher resolution tiles for the USFS / USGS layers - the ones hosted by CalTopo seem to handle overzooming better. That, or the ability to sideload my own maps using mbtiles.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback. Feature requests please to support@atlogis.com. Mbtiles support(and other raster formats) will come soon.

content: In the last 10 years this is the fourth app like this that I have purchased. This by far is the simplest most precise app I have found. We hunt in some very dense wooded areas and when it starts to snow you can become disoriented. If you lay down a track as you go you will find your way back. Having every topographical map in the United States in my pocket is not a bad thing either.

Overall I knew what to expect from the free app and I liked the features. With the pro version, I liked the idea of being able to import from kml files and other formats. Unfortunately, it was just that -- an idea. It was unable to see any of my files of directories. Had /storage/self/ and /storage/emulated/ but that was it. On my device, the internal storage is at /storage/emulated/0/ (within which the app stores its maps and cache). So...who knows. Maybe I will try it another time...
replyContent: Please contact support@atlogis.com

content: Absolutely the best GPS app I have ever used since the smart phone was invented. However, needs calibration and units tool for each measurement because the altimeter is off by 100 feet.
Does everything is says

Wish I could import .tif and .PDF maps. Would also like to see it work with Dropbox. Great potential. Avenza started charging 129.99$ a year for unlimited use of PDF maps. This looks like the next best thing.
Allows user to view the actual path and/or coordinates rather than being lead blindly turn by turn. One may plan rest stops, photo ops, etc. Not perfect,  but close to it, (...so far...)
Great app
Great maps, lots of info and options.

I do a lot of back country where no cell service. Over a large area. Caching should have better tools to download all zoom levels over a large area. Having to go around at level 15 to make sure u have everything I need in the area I'm going is a pain in the ass and unreliable.
replyContent: Please use Menu/Cache Map to download all maptiles for your area of interest.

content: Great in the woods.
I wish they would add navigation. I know there is somewhat of navigation, but it's as the crow flies and does not use road integration.
Choice of good maps. Accurate tracking. Import and export capabilities.  Easy on the battery.
Its a very good App. I use it when I am out horseback riding and hiking. What is stopping me from making this a great app (5) is the ability to download the routes on my home computer.
Best map so far I have used also love the fact that I can down load to my phone form desktop

the point in me buying this app was to be able to share my location with my family while im in the woods hunting just in case something were to happen to me and when they try to use the link to google maps the locations are not even close im talking not even the right city. so I have wasted $12 for nothing . everything else I need is in the free version.
replyContent: you need activate "locate me" button (or start track rec or goto nav ) and wait for GPS signal before sharing location. You can set data field to "accuracy" to see current location accuracy.

content: So much better than a Garmin device. Have used this for a couple years, never had issues connecting to GPS in the middle of no where. It is very accurate, and doesn't eat batteries while tracking - just make sure to put your device in airplane mode if you don't have a network signal. Highly  recommend  the Pro Version, worth every cent.
I use topographic maps a lot to hunt public land. I've been using it for a few seasons now and I can't complain at all. PRE DOWNLOAD YOUR MAPS IF YOU EXPECT TO BE OUT OF SERVICE RANGE!
This app is awesome. Much easier to use than any gps I have ever tried. I bought the full version and well worth $11. It does what I need and accurate.
Love this app with one exception picture waypoints

Love it... Everyone in my hunting party was jealous even though they had expensive Garmin GPS units. Just need to download maps before you go but even if you don't you can still use the tracks on a blank background. Wish you could do more while recording a track... Would like to be able to add a goto way point while I am still recording a track Also would like a way to export tracks to my Google account.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback ! You can add a goto waypoint during track recording. You can also export tracks to Google Earth KMZ format.

content: I like it.
Use it all the time for running and biking in new areas. Has a more intuitive UI than any of the other navigation apps out there. Wish total ascent/descent were available data fields. Thx.
Love the app. Didn't use my Garmin once on the last hunting trip. Would like to see the ability to send a map with weigh points to another user.

My wife and I took a maze of dirt roads out into the desert before stopping so that she could do some night photography.   I didn't think about it on the way in, but without being able to see the landmarks getting out would be a nightmare.  Luckily I had turned on tracking and used the "track back" feature to guide us back out.  The first major choice our instincts told us the wrong direction.  Best app I ever bought.

For highly recommended apps, such as this one, I read the one star reviews looking for a pattern that may indicate a problem with the app that may affect my devices or intended use. For this app I recommend using the app before rating it; make use of the excellent technical support.  This app is everything it promises to be and more. Despite the odd complaints about the UI, I found the UI to be intuitive and appropriately layered from novice to expert trekker. Use the app before you rate it.

I very seldom give a 5 star review. However this app is perfect. It works. I can put in coordinate way points, I can download entire regions, etc. It is awesome, and instead of spending 100.00 with Garmin, this only cost $11.00

Import tracks and waypoints (.gpx or .kml), choose map type (scanned topo is -the best-), follow the track, id waypoints on the way, record track, export to Google earth. Oh yes, most valuable - can cache any map, any geographic area, for off line use. This app has everything I can imagine I will ever need.
The most useful GPS map app.  Has served me well, particularly when traveling places where Google maps doesn't work.
Great App
Love it easy to read and manage.

I really like this app, but one factor stops me from rating it 5 stars. User friendly interface, easy to cache maps of many types, adjustable resolution for zooming in, all in all great!.  That one factor? The cache where maps are stored is in the onboard memory, and is not able to be moved to the exterior SD card slot, at least not for a Samsung Galaxy Tab 2/ Android 4.2.2.   I want to cache a large map with high resolution. My tablet has 8GB of memory, about 1/2 taken up by the operating system. I have a 32GB exterior SD card for additional memory, but Atlogis cannot access it.  So I am stuck with a large map with limited resolution, with many GBs of memory and no way to use it...  If it werent for this, the app would do exactly what I want to do, and I would rate it tops. But for now, with no fix from support after weeks of waiting, I have to give it 3 stars. I'd be happy to edit this review, if the problem can be fixed.
Love this app it's amazing and works great up here in Alaska thank you

I use this app now as my primary hiking GPS unit. I can set up a tour in Google Earth and cache the maps then use it in real time on my hike. It also allows me to record the hike which I can reload into Earth and review.

I like this app and use it every time I  go out hiking. I just upgraded to Pro, but was disappointed to see my old tracks no longer accessible. Be forewarned that you should back up your old tracks before upgrading to Pro.
The US forest service maps in my area that I'm hunting do not exist on this app...Forest service roads are not marked...Only good for a small portion of the state (Az) $10 bucks down the drain...

If there is a weakness I haven't found it yet. We use this app for hiking and it really suits our purposes well. It is capable of far more than what we use it for, so the sky is the limit for outdoor activities. I particularly enjoy the maps that provide directional heading guides for use with lensatic compasses so you can enjoy some of the more challenging and pure methods of navigation if that is something that you enjoy. Former military guys with land nav experience might appreciate that.

We use this for all of our hiking and kayaking trips and it is accurate, reliable and fun to review older trips in map view. Wish there was an easy way to share the recorded trips as many trails aren't documented that well.

It does everything I need it to do. I find it easy to use.
Hunt, hike, bike, or 4x4. If you do any of these you WILL use this app. Unmatched.

This app takes care of everything, and more. It does the research for you, u can create waypoints (to mark whatever), and the fact that it keeps EVERYTHING on your device. GET IT.

content: I've been using this software to record hikes and bike rides and it is my favorite app for this task.  It is a great example of sensibly  designed and well thought out for what features you might choose to use, with all it's options performing as described.  My compliments

content: Very comprehensive with very many layer options available. Offline storage of many layers extremely helpful when no cell service is available. I recommend this to many people.
to hide Waypoints.

replyContent: GPS-Accuracy depends on GPS-signal strenght. You can set "Accuracy" in data-field to see your current accuracy in feet. With a free sky accuracy should be below 10 feet. Other apps will have same accuracy. You can export your track to KML wich can be imported by most CAD and GIS.

replyContent: We've answered Joes requests over and over again. He just ignores them and posts negative reviews over and over again. We think he must be in charge of one of the companies he mentions! ;) Regards.

content: I was looking for an app that had the USGS topo maps.  This is it.  Great app!
Love it
Great app! Particularly the pro version. Used it in Alaska to follow position on wilderness float trip. Worked flawlessly.

Purchased pro after giving the free version a test run and for the most part, it does a good job. I use it mostly for hiking and have not had any issues with it losing its GPS signal unlike the previous app I was using. A few suggestions for improvement...the ability to export/share/backup multiple tracks at the same time (in GPX, KMZ, KML format), the ability to see tracks across different devices (sync type function), the backup/import process is a bit on the cumbersome side, especially for someone who may not know how to navigate through their device to find the backup file, and a free floating zoom. Sometimes the zoom is too small or too big since it snaps to a specific size. While hiking, being able to minimize the app while tracking progress would be a plus. It's possible already but using the back button brings up a dialog saying the app will close (something to that tune).  While I do see room for improvement, overall, this is a well functioning app that I didn't mind paying for.
Hunters and outsdoors well worth the money! Love this app!

content: If you have plenty of storage space and cache your maps ahead of time, this map app is pretty sweet for offroad use. One oddity I noticed recently:  I have version 4.0.6 on my phone and 4.0.7 on my tablet, and on my phone, I can select the exact folder to use for my map cache, but on my tablet, I can only select the device, and the folder path is set.

I use it for Northern Nevada and the various maps allow for a a ton of info and I love it's tracking and simplicity.  Being able to select a spot get the lat long and elevation is great.  I was on the fence about the pro version but glad I got it. I shouldn't have waited so long.
Excellent app, as a fire fighter / EMT I use this app alot . Works well in all environments.

Great app. 1.Once in a while when in the field it won't load a map at all but will still record your track and you can view it later when it will load. If it werent for that, id give it 5 stars. 2. I have been using this app for at least a year now and it is the best location/gps app that i have seen. They resolved some of the minor issues so i now have to give it 5 stars! Its really great! Best topo app on the web.  Buy the pro version!
If you export a KML file from Google Earth with waypoints and tracks, US Topo Maps will only import the waypoints. I consider that to be a basic feature that an $11 app should include. 2 thumbs down.
replyContent: You should be able to import tracks from a kml file. Please send us the file in question so that we can check what is going wrong. Thanks!

content: So far so good. I like it better then the Trimble app i had been using, but i feel as though there is no support for this product at all. Where is the web site? How do i ask questions? I would like o now if there is a way to download maps to my computer from this company and then install them, since it takes hours to do it on the phone. Anybody out there? I emailed the company but got no response.
Nice details and overlays.

Overall, I'm very impressed with the app. However, I needed it on a hunting trip with no cellular coverage and hence needed to cache the maps. It takes forever with lots of failures. Please investigate. Also, a bit overpriced in my opinion.
Excellent app for in the woods.
Easier to use than BCN in my opinion.   Great for offroad use, showed all know roads and trails
Great for backcountry tracking (without data/network), when you use the "cache" function to download to your phone/tablet. Love it. Flawless and snappy.

Nice app, but they have lost some functionality in one of the recent updates. You can no longer easily show all way points on the map, you have to individually select each one, which is tedious. There used to be an option to just show all of them.
I use GPS Viking on the laptop, and this is the closest I found to it. Wonderful app for logging trails exploring in the jeep or on the bike.
Great app for maps!

This is the best program that seamlessly removes the USGS Topo map collars.  Downloads work very good for usings a tablet in the field.  You can save gpx files for downloading into other programs.  A real neat options allows you to download various types of maps, like nautical maps.   You also can various overlays on, like wind vector maps from  NOAA. Very good program at a reasonable cost.
Best GPS app period.  Airplane mode and GPS on = all day GPS.

I bumped it up to a 4 for giving us NAD27 but its only on lat lon. Need it most on UTM for working search and rescue missions with USGS topo maps.  Any plans for this option in the future?  Other than that, it's the best topo app I've used for user friendly system! Keep improving!
I like this app it would be better if it would give  measurements in feet anything under a mile  when you use the go to option

You can't rotate the map. It would be nice if you could move the x and y axis of the map. Mediocre app. Limited use in Alaska. Backcountry navigator is better don't waste your money on this one as I did.

I tried to email the link in the app but it is returned every time.   Maybe you can answer my question in this medium.          QUESTION.  how do I direct my cached maps to be saved on my SD card ??  A DETAILED step by step would be appreciated!   I did everything that's in your help file to no avail.

This Pro app is easy to use,  works very well in the back country without service assuming you downloaded the areas (and routes/waypoints if wanted) ahead of time.  It's easy to import routes and display them overlaid on the topo and can even record your own routes for future reference/sharing.  Would be better if you could see which areas you'd downloaded without having to go into airplane mode of you could associate a set of waypoints as a single file for ease of use, but otherwise works as I'd want.
TOPOGRAPHY MAP APP I like it,great when In hiking.

One of, if not THE best topo app available. BUT as other users have pointed out, there is no indication which tiles are downloaded. Other apps I have used in the past have clearly indicated this either directly on the maps or in a tile mode (including scale/detail downloaded). This app does not. This means you must a) pre-plan every outing and hope you have all the tiles you need, or b) download tons of data for any area you might possibly go and hope you have all the tiles you need.

USGS paper topo maps have been hard to source in Alaska (and are about to become near impossible with the imminent closure of the Map Store in Anchorage) so this app makes those beautiful and authoritative maps available and augmented them with GPS tech, making this app essential for serious trip planners coming to the USA.
Very professional and well thought out user interface.
Great app. I use it mostly for the USGS 7 1/2 minute topo maps along with the GPS and electronic compass. It's all right there in my hand. Thanks

I have the pro version, & I love being able to download maps for offline use. This app is so much better than others like it, and I love being able to import KML files! My only gripe is that you can't hide the start and finish points on tracks.
Not a very techy person, how does one download maps for offline use?? Also where could I find good Arial maps to download to my device? Thanks
Works better than any other gps app. I have used
Only Google maps were visible the rest are blurred
Loved that it can be saved offline. I used it hiking the sawtooth mountains last week and loved it. Worked great.

Works very well on my Razr. You knuckleheads leaving bad reviews of this product need to learn how to read & take the time tweak the settings. I've tried most of similar products and this one is, by far, the best.

Superior functionality - this works way better than my backcountry GPS.  I used this on an overnight alpine rock climb in the North Cascaes 2 weeks ago.  Was able to overlay prior GPX tracks - awesome!

This app does exactly what I need it to.  No subscription and only 11 bux what a deal!  Been using this app for past year and have not been let down yet.  I believe its the only app that lets u cache to sd card as well.
Very well done. LOTS of really nice functions. Works perfectly. I love it.
I tried at least 4 other offline map apps and this was head and shoulders above the rest.

One of the most useful features of a topo mapping app is the ability to download map areas for offline use.   An important aspect of this is the ability to know which areas you've downloaded. ATLOGIS seems to have overlooked this essential capability:  there is no way that I have found, to visually verify which map areas have been downloaded for offline use.  You have to just overshoot and hope that you've got all the right areas covered, because once you're in the bush and out of signal, it's too late.
False advertiding. Cannoy download offlind maps. Useless in back country. Waste waste waste grrrrrrr
replyContent: Use the "Bulk Download" feature to download (free) map tiles for offline usage !

content: I haven't had a single problem with this, as of yet.
Great hunting tool. Mark spots. Track animal movement. ..endless possibilities.
This is one of the best topographic and geographic map systems to come along in a long time.
Weather radar doesn't work. Can't do a bulk download. Can't add new route points.  Wasted $11.03
replyContent: Please contact support@atlogis.com to find out your problem or request a refund.

content: Bing and google images are more than a year old.  Its got us shoppin for a more current app.
replyContent: There a several layers with aerials. The USGS orthos are often the most recent images.

content: Works great, best backcountry map app I've come across.
Very good tool for the back yard, and professional weather people out there!
I used the record feature to track my movements while camping. Kept it on and hooked up to a solar charger. No problem
Altimeter does not work well outside the us
replyContent: Altimeter accuracy depends on GPS signal strength not on location.

content: Used with a moto x this app is better for hiking than any GPS I've used, except professional models for field mapping.

Some of the reviews I read were complaining about the topo maps being older but just depends on what you are using them for. As someone searching for more historical things, it has led me to places I probably wouldn't have found otherwise. Plus, with all the layers you can use, it should have a tool for whatever you need. The waypoints and the navigation have been dead on.      I do wish that there was a "logon" or something so I could use on more than my phone. I dont want to buy again to use on my tablet

With no option to automatically live update your location the only way to use this app for navigation (without recording an unwanted track) is to constantly hit the GPS button, a very frustrating deal breaker.  The app ignores some of it's preferences as well, such as turning off the "location acquired" chime (which gets annoying real fast with the above issue).  It would also be nice if a loaded GPX would stay overlayed on the map until switched off.  Fix these, and I'd give it 5 stars without hesitation.
It would be nice in goto to pick multiple points and have app calculate total distance.

Works as advertised. I use the old topo maps to find areas like old mine dumps and abandoned towns while on my atv. Works great when maps are cached. Took a while to learn functions, but I am not a tech-head.
Many features at your fingertips. Little pricy for what it is though.
Recommended
Solid app. Fair amount of options. A bit pricey. Would like to see ability to rotate screen similar to GE.
I use this to plan my hikes and hunts. Being able to switch layers makes this mapping program extremely useful for planning.

Updated jan 6, 2014.  I have been using this app for 5 months. I use backcountry navigator too. Pros: the us topo maps are the best. They color in rivers you can't see in the us topo bc navigator provides. The  choice of maps are the best.  You can now zoom in to level  15. Cons: waypoints and  tracks. Easier to organize trips on bc navigator.
We downloaded 200 mb of maps before going into the wilderness for 7 days.  Worked great, including low battery usage while tracking our progress.  Well worth the price.  Nexus 7.
I've used it on several OHV trails in AZ and it worked flawlessly.

Thanks dev.  Tried the free version and liked it so i purchased.  I've used this for hunting this last season and it made a huge difference while driving game with the compass.  Many features,  worth the purchase.
Perfect for topo scouting prehunt!
Fantastic topo app!
Any further comment I give is simply to make it even better. For data publishing I do need access to choosing or at least knowledge of the datum. Cannot find what is used. Hopefully NAD83...
replyContent: Datum for coordinates is WGS84

content: Everything works as stated including the GPS feature even when you do not have WiFi.  My Google nexus tablet does not have 4g data capability yet I am able to use it in the woods with no WiFi.  Love it.
Thank You.
Great tool for deer hunting
Nice maps

Used it on a bushwack hike to a mountain lake involving a lot of terrain.  The track recording feature was vital in both getting there and retracing our route.  Once home I could see both tracks simultaneously on the topo map to compare.  I also like the low learning curve compared to competing apps I've purchased that aren't as well thought out.
No overseas topo map coverage.  This is the only reason I downloaded this app  Only reason it gets a two and only reason I'll keep it as it gives a mgrs grid and o can (hopefully) load my own maps.
replyContent:
Nomen est Omen ...
You can use Google, Bing and OpenStreetMaps layers outside US

content: Was impressed with the utility of the free version, even without cell service and bought the PRO version.  A reminder, if using a PAD  TABLET or a none mobile serviced old Android phone, the Google walllet permits a buy without re-starting mobile service (via wifi).  Also wanted the extra map features and extra way points for route tracking, geocaching etc. 5 STARS
Haven't gotten lost yet so either dementia hasn't set in or it works.
Need print option
Like what I see so far.
A measuring tool, such as the one in previous versions of google maps would really round out this app.
replyContent: Measuring tool will come with one of the next updates.

content: Used this on a hunting trip in the Colorado mointains. Did everything I hoped for and more! Is there a way to use this for geocaching? Then it would be 6 stars!

Just used this app on my droid 4 while backpacking in the Ansel Adams Wilderness. Worked perfectly. On a typical day my phones battery last about 6 hours. Huge concern for the hike. But the gps works in airplane mode, with all other program services killed and airplane mode enabled I got 2.5 days of battery life.

Using for day hikes on Blue Ridge. Distances are serial point to point with go to functions, and battery consumption is a bit high (turn off wifi and turn on airplane mode).  Hoever a solid app without paying for a dedicated gps unit.
Great app.  Use it especially when hunting.  Never get lost now!  Hallelujah

a couple of suggestions for future releases - increase zoom and make it persistent so text is easier to read - get it to auto-update GPS position and navigate along downloaded GPS tracks  (but need to balance update rate to avoid being a battery hog)  and a bug I think... - on at least one tile the altitudes were in meters and did not respond to meters /  feet control (Sourdough trail area,  up Boulder Canyon)  Overall a very good early release - will get 5 stars if updates / bug fixes come fast enough
replyContent: You need to start a track recording or a GoTo/Route-Navigation to auto-update GPS-position. You can increase zoom with long-click on zoom-button. We have no influence on imprinted altitudes units on USGS topo maps.

content: Topos for our area are from 1945, and they work well, but there are newer maps that are not included. Usgs redid them in the early 2000s. Otherwise the ap works well.
replyContent: You need to select the US Topo Quads layer to see the most recent US Topo maps.

content: I would give 6 stars if it were possible.
The app works great and has some very cool features, but the topo maps for Arizona are at least ten years old.
replyContent: The age of the traditional USGS DRGs differs from region to region. To see the most recent topo maps select the US Topo quads layer. Nevertheless you'll find the older DRGs very usefull to find small tracks/pathes.

content: Nice UI!
Excelllent
This app treated me very well on various hikes in glacier national park this summer. It tend to crash from time to time but seems to fill in track gaps fairly well.
Great simple GPS
Love the app... cant find the map key though :(
Works great. :)
Disappointed with lack of zoom on my great screen. Hope to see improvement soon! Has potential but not there yet.
This is COOL! Finally, a program with decent, downloadable Alaskan USGS maps. Very happy :)
Very small letters hard to read street names.
Would be a 5 if saved waypoints would stay on the map as opposed to having to select them each time you open the app.
Please please fix this app so zoom is persistent.

This is a great app and it's very useful. The information about speed and altitude, including graphs, is very cool. It's also excellent for offline GPS use. The only issue is that it does not zoom in incredibly close, making routes by foot somewhat difficult to track on the map. I haven't seen another app as functional out there, though.

Downloading maps for offline use is convenient.  Would benefit from more gps info while on the move - ie, I want to see speed, elevation, lat, long, etc on the same screen as the map, not on a subscreen.  I just used this for a 650 mile offroad trip and was pleased with it.  Though the text on the maps is difficult to see while driving, even on a 10 in tablet.  Well worth the very low price.

Crashes when try to see layers. Can't see elevation of GPS points (don't know if that's a function of the GPS on my phone). Won't download all the maps in the zoom area visible and won't recognize the mobile network to do this. Would like to be able to zoom in further.
replyContent: Please contact android@atlogis.com and give us a chance to check/fix it.

content: Thorough and accurate. Has many levels of knowledge and tracks accurately. Wish zoom was closer but great overall
Just used on a 15 mile trip. Very detailed summary at end of hike to help break the hike down. Would recommend especially if you like going backpacking.
Nice app but the zoom level does not go high enough for close back country work.
Love the feature that allows you to switch between different data sources. Too bad Google and Bing don't allow offline storage.
Not intuitive, help not helpful, waste of money.

The app in itself is very easy to use. I quickly added way points for my upcoming trip. Problem is the 'pro' version (or any of its versions that I can see) will not allow you to zoom in enough for hiking purposes. You can expand with two fingers and see the map resolution is there but once you let go it springs out.  This is a deal breaker in my opinion.

This is a very impressive app that loads and performs just great. When coupled with my solar charger and extra battery pack it makes field work a joy. Bringing together what would normally be several pounds of field guides via other apps with this now as a high end GPS, well, in short this is stunning for those of us that grew up in the age of the abacus. To then bridge it further with radar overlays (when cell phone service is available) in this app is just the cat's meow. I tip my hat to the developer(s). I have no problem zooming in or out, or any other functionality. I'd encourage anyone even remotely interested in using quads on their tablets to give it a try and save themselves the $350 a high end GPS would cost.

Super easy to use and great maps to pick from including reliable USGS topos and the newer version National Map as well as others. On road navigation routes from other apps can be combined by easily importing .gpx files. Excellent product.

This app is the best and easiest app for woodland navigation. I run a Law Enforcement woodland special ops team and I have tried many nav apps. The ease of use for this one is the best out there. The options you have are unbelievable. Bought the pro version and I don't pay for apps often.
